<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Git Guide</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Ubuntu+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400;1,700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <span>
        <h1>Git Starter Guide</h1>
        <p>By Alex Dombroski</p>
      </span>
      <p>
        Git is a free command line tool that allows people to collaborate and
        version control files. Understanding the basic commands helps you
        understand how git based GUI tools work. This cheat sheet gives an intro
        to basic, useful commands.
      </p>
    </header>
    <main class="two">
      <!-- --------------- Column One --------------- -->
      <section>
        <article>
          <h2>Installation</h2>
          <nav>
            <p>Install Git:</p>
            <a href="https://git-scm.com">https://git-scm.com</a>
            <p>Create Github Account:</p>
            <a href="https://github.com/join">https://github.com/join</a>
          </nav>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Configuration</h2>
          <div>
            <p class="small">git config --global [option] [value]</p>
            <p class="small">git config --local [option] [value]</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            Options can be set globally your the file system or locally to the
            repo folder. Local options override global options.
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git config list</span> to list
            <span class="command">--global</span> or
            <span class="command">--local</span> configurations
          </p>

          <h3 class="ul-title">Common Configuration Options</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>user.name</strong>: Set your name for commits
              <span class="command">user.name [first last]</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>user.email</strong>: Set your email for commits
              <span class="command">user.email [email]</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>core.editor</strong>: Define the default text editor
              <span class="command">core.editor [editor]</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>color.ui</strong>: Enable colored output
              <span class="command">color.ui auto</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            All Config options:
            <a href="https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config"
              >https://git-scm.com/docs/git-config</a
            >
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="repo-setup">
          <h2>Repo Setup</h2>
          <div class="two">
            <div>
              <p>git init</p>
              <p>git remote add [name] [url]</p>
            </div>
            <p>git clone [url]</p>
          </div>
          <p><span class="command">git init</span> creates a brand new repo</p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git clone</span> creates a local branch of an existing
            repository
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="break">Saving Changes</h2>
          <div class="two">
            <p class="span">git status</p>
            <p>git diff</p>
            <p>git diff --staged</p>
            <p>git add [file] [file2]</p>
            <p>git add .</p>
            <p>git commit</p>
            <p>git commit -m "[message]"</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git diff</span> shows changes not yet staged or
            commited
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git add .</span> will stage all files for the next
            commit.
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git commit --amend</span> modifies the last commit
            (don't use on already merged/pushed commits)
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git reset [file]</span> is the "undo" to add
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Logging & History</h2>
          <div class="two">
            <p>git log</p>
            <p>git log --oneline</p>
          </div>
          <p>See commit history</p>

          <div>
            <p>git show [commit]</p>
          </div>
          <p>Show details about a commit by specifying a commit hash</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Undo Commits</h2>
          <div>
            <p>git revert [commit]</p>
          </div>
          <p>Create a new commit to undo a previous</p>

          <div class="two">
            <div>
              <p>git reset HEAD~1</p>
              <p>git retore .</p>
            </div>
            <p>git reset --hard HEAD~1</p>
          </div>
          <p>Permanatly deletes a previous commit</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Useful Files</h2>
          <p>
            <strong>.gitignore</strong> choose files to be ignored by git such as
            <span class="command">.env</span>,
            <span class="command">logs/</span>,
            <span class="command">dist/</span>, or a
            <span class="command">pattern*/</span>
          </p>

          <p>Gitignore Documentation:</p>
          <a href="https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore"
            >https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore</a
          >

          <p>
            Use a <strong>.gitkeep</strong> file to track an empty directory.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article id="help">
          <p>
            Check <a href="https://git-scm.com/doc">https://git-scm.com/doc</a> or
            run <span class="command">git help [command]</span> for more information
            about commands
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <!-- --------------- Column Two --------------- -->
      <section>
        <article>
          <h2>Switching Branches</h2>
          <p><span class="command">git branch</span> to view all branches</p>
          <div class="two">
            <p>git switch [branch]</p>
            <p>git checkout [branch]</p>
            <p>git switch -c [branch]</p>
            <p>git checkout -b [branch]</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            Use <span class="command">-c</span> or
            <span class="command">-b</span> to create a new branch before moving.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Merging/Rebasing Branches</h2>
          <div class="two">
            <p class="span">*Commit Changes in from-branch</p>
            <p class="span">git diff [from-branch]..[to-branch]</p>
            <p>git switch [to-branch]</p>
            <p>git checkout [to-branch]</p>
            <p>git merge [from-branch]</p>
            <p>git rebase [from-branch]</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git branch -D [from-branch]</span> optionally to
            delete branch after merge
          </p>

          <h3>Resolving Conflicts</h3>
          <p>
            While rebasing/merging, use the
            <span class="command">--continue</span> to finish merging after resolving
            conflicts
          </p>
          <p>
            While rebasing/merging, use the
            <span class="command">--abort</span> to give up after failing to resolve
            conflicts
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Git Remotes</h2>
          <div>
            <p>git remote -v</p>
            <p>git remote add [name] [url]</p>
            <p>git remote remove [name] [url]</p>
            <p>git remote set-url [name] [url]</p>
          </div>
          <p>Common remote names are origin and upstream</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="break small">Pushing Changes to Remote Branch</h2>
          <div class="two">
            <p>git push</p>
            <p>git push [remote] [branch]</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git push -u [remote] [branch]</span> Sets the upstream
            for future pushes so the command can be run in the future with only git
            push
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git push --force</span> overwrites the remote branch
          </p>

          <p>
            <span class="command"
              >git config --global push.autoSetupRemote true</span
            >
            configures an option to never have to set upstream for branches
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="small">Pulling Changes from Remote Branch</h2>
          <div class="two">
            <p>git pull</p>
            <div>
              <p>git fetch</p>
              <p>git merge</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git pull --rebase</span> to avoid merge commits
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Store Changes Temporarily</h2>
          <div class="two left">
            <p>git stash</p>
            <p>git stash push -m "[message]"</p>
            <p>git stash pop</p>
            <p>git stash pop stash@{'{#}'}</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git stash -u</span> to also stash away untracked
            files
          </p>
          <p class="ul-title">Times when stashing is useful:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>To switch a branch without commiting</li>
            <li>Move changes after forgetting to branch from main</li>
            <li>Testing different sets of changes</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git stash apply</span> applys a stash without deleteing
            it like <span class="command">pop</span>
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git stash list</span> shows the stash stack
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git stash pop</span> will run
            <span class="command">git stash pop stash@{'{0}'}</span> by defualt
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git stash drop</span> deletes the latest stash
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git stash clear</span> deletes all stashes
            <span class="command">pop</span>
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2>Deleting Files</h2>
          <p>
            <span class="command">git clean -fd</span> remove all untracked files
            or specify a pattern
          </p>
          <p>
            Use the <span class="command">-n</span> flag to preview files to be deleted
          </p>
          <p>
            <span class="command">-X</span> removes ignored files and
            <span class="command">-x</span> removes ignored and untracked files
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

<script>
  // Create a spotlight element
  const spotlight = document.createElement('div');
  spotlight.classList.add('spotlight');
  document.body.appendChild(spotlight);

  // Update the spotlight position based on mouse movement
  document.body.addEventListener('mousemove', (e) => {
    // Use pageX and pageY to account for scrolling
    const x = e.pageX;
    const y = e.pageY;

    spotlight.style.top = `${y}px`; // Center spotlight vertically
    spotlight.style.left = `${x}px`; // Center spotlight horizontally
  });

  document.body.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
    spotlight.style.opacity = '0'; // Hide spotlight when leaving the document.body
  });

  document.body.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
    spotlight.style.opacity = '1'; // Show spotlight when entering the document.body
  });
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --primary-dark-color: #222823;
    --secondary-dark-color: #3b453c;
    --primary-light-color: #e1e2ff;
    --accent1-color: #99ff15;
    --accent2-color: #99ff15;

    --spotlight-gap: 3px;
  }

  body {
    font-family:
      'Ubuntu Mono', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue',
      sans-serif;
    background-color: var(--primary-dark-color);
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--spotlight-gap);
    padding-top: 0px;
  }

  header > span {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;

    & p {
      margin: 0;
    }
  }

  a:link,
  a:visited,
  p,
  h1,
  h2,
  h3,
  h4,
  h5,
  li {
    color: var(--primary-light-color);
  }

  a {
    display: block;
    color: black;
  }

  p {
    margin: 10px auto;
  }

  h1,
  h2,
  h3,
  h4,
  h5 {
    font-family:
      'Trebuchet MS', 'Lucida Sans Unicode', 'Lucida Grande', 'Lucida Sans',
      Arial, sans-serif;
  }

  h2 {
    border-bottom: 3px var(--secondary-dark-color) dashed;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }

  h2.small {
    font-size: 20px;
  }

  p.small {
    font-size: 9px;
  }

  ul {
    margin-top: 0px;
    padding-left: 30px;
  }

  main {
    gap: var(--spotlight-gap);
  }

  article,
  header {
    background-color: var(--primary-dark-color);
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 1px;
    margin: var(--spotlight-gap) 0px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
  }
  header {
    margin: 0;
  }

  div > p {
    background-color: var(--primary-dark-color);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 25px;
    height: 100%;
    align-content: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  div {
    display: grid;
    margin: 10px auto;
    text-align: center;
    align-items: center;
    column-gap: 2px;
    row-gap: 2px;

    border: 2px solid var(--secondary-dark-color);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background-color: var(--secondary-dark-color);

    overflow: hidden;
  }

  div > div {
    border: none;
    margin: 0 auto;
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 0;
  }

  .two {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .left {
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 3fr;
  }

  .span {
    grid-column-end: span 2;
  }

  .command {
    background-color: var(--secondary-dark-color);
    color: var(--accent1-color);
    padding: 2px 3px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    font-size: 12px;
  }

  .ul-title {
    margin-bottom: 5px;
  }

  p:has(+ a) {
    margin-bottom: 5px;
  }

  #help a {
    display: inline;
  }

  :global(.spotlight) {
    z-index: -1;
    position: absolute;
    width: 0px;
    height: 0px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent1-color);
    pointer-events: none; /* Makes it unclickable */
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px 50px var(--accent1-color);
  }

  @media print {
    * {
      -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact !important;
      color-adjust: exact !important;
      print-color-adjust: exact !important;
    }
    @page {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    div {
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .break {
      page-break-before: always;
    }

    a {
      text-underline-offset: 4px;
    }
    main {
      gap: 10px;
    }
    :global(.spotlight) {
      display: none;
    }
    .repo-setup {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    #help {
      display: none;
    }
  }
</style>
